      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A stockpot or large saucepan with a lid. The barley needs room to swell.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Build the base",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If using dried porcini, lift them from their soaking water and roughly chop; strain the soaking liquid through a fine sieve. Bring the {{stock-chicken}} to a simmer in a large pot. Add the {{pearl-barley}}, {{onion}}, {{carrot}}, {{parsnip}}, {{celeriac}}, {{leek}}, {{bay-leaves}}, and {{allspice}}. If using porcini, add them now along with their strained soaking liquid.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Simmer until thick",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Simmer partially covered for 45 to 55 minutes, until the barley is completely tender and has thickened the broth. The soup should be thick. If it seems thin, simmer uncovered for another 10 minutes. Season with {{sea-salt-fine}} and {{black-pepper-ground}}. Remove the bay leaves and allspice berries.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Finish and serve",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Stir in the {{unsalted-butter}} if using, then ladle into bowls and scatter with {{dill}}. Serve with bread.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Continue simmering until the barley is completely tender with no chalky core. Older barley can take up to 70 minutes",
              "cause": "Not cooked long enough",
              "symptom": "Barley still chalky in the centre"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Add more hot stock or water, a ladleful at a time, and stir to incorporate. Adjust seasoning after thinning",
              "cause": "Too little stock or cooked uncovered too long",
              "symptom": "Soup too thick"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Add a small splash of cider vinegar to lift the soup. Dried porcini make a substantial difference to the broth depth",
              "cause": "Stock too light or no dried mushrooms",
              "symptom": "Flat, muted flavour"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this dish lives",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Krupnik appears in nearly every Polish regional tradition. It was long associated with peasant cooking: bone broth, whatever roots were available, and barley from the store. In modern Polish home cooking, it remains a default soup for illness, cold weather, and feeding children. The dill added at the end is non-negotiable in Polish households. The soup improves markedly on the second day, once the barley has had time to absorb the broth and the flavours have deepened.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
